{"title_page": "Vishera River (Perm Krai)", "text_new": "{{Other uses|Vishera River (disambiguation)}}\n{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}}\n\n{{Infobox river\n| name              = Vishera River\n| image             = Vishera.jpg\n| image_size        = \n| image_alt         =\n| image_caption     = View of the [[Tulymsky Kamen]] mountain range from the banks of the Vishera\n| map               = Kama basin.png\n| map_size          = 200 \n| map_alt           =\n| map_caption       = Scheme of the Kama River Basin.\n| source1_location  = North Ural\n| mouth             = [[Kama River]]\n| subdivision_type1 = Country\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Russia]]\n| progression       = {{RKama}}\n| length            = {{convert|415|km|mi|abbr=on}} \n| source1_elevation = \n| mouth_coordinates = {{coord|59|54|14|N|56|26|20|E|source:kolossus-ruwiki|display=it}}\n| discharge1_avg    = {{convert|457|m3/s|cuft/s|abbr=on}} \n| basin_size        = {{convert|31,200|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} \n| tributaries_left  =\n| tributaries_right =\n}}\n\nThe '''Vishera River''' ({{lang-ru|\u0412\u0438\u0448\u0435\u0440\u0430}}) is a river in [[Perm Krai]], [[Russia]], a [[:wikt:left bank|left bank]] tributary of the [[Kama River]]. It is {{convert|415|km|mi}} long, and its [[drainage basin]] covers {{convert|31200|km2|mi2}}.<ref name=gvr>[http://textual.ru/gvr/index.php?card=180376 \u00ab\u0420\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0412\u0418\u0428\u0415\u0420\u0410\u00bb], Russian State Water Registry</ref><ref>http://www.feow.org/ecoregion_details.php?eco=410</ref> The Vishera River freezes in late October or early November and stays under the ice until the end of April. There are [[diamond]] deposits in the basin of the Vishera River.\n\nThe Vishera used to be part of the [[Cherdyn Road]] and is still considered one of the most picturesque rivers of the Urals. It starts on the extreme northeast of Perm Krai, near the border with the [[Komi Republic]] and [[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]. It flows on the west foothills of Ural Mountains and is a mountain river for most of its length. There are many rapids and shoals in the channel and many rocks along its banks. \n\nThe [[Vishera Nature Reserve]] is along the upper reaches of the river.\n\n'''Main tributaries (from source to mouth):'''<ref name=gvr/>\n* Left: [[Niols River|Niols]], [[Moyva River|Moyva]], [[Vels River|Vels]], [[Uls River|Uls]], [[Akchim River|Akchim]], [[Yazva River|Yazva]], [[Vizhaikha River|Vizhaikha]];\n* Right: [[Lypya River|Lypya]], [[Yelva River|Yelva]], [[Bolshaya Vaya River|Bolshaya Vaya]], [[Pisanka River|Pisanka]], [[Govorukha River|Govorukha]], [[Kolva River, Perm Krai|Kolva]].\n\n== Etymology ==\nKomi people call the river ''Viser''. Experts in the Komi language noticed that this element is also in names of other rivers in Ural. [[Aleksandr Matveyev (linguist)|A. K. Matveyev]] supposes that Vishera can mean ''Northern River'' or ''Midnight River'' (in [[Sami languages]]).\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://enc.permculture.ru/showObject.do?object=1803757360&idParentObject=1803883941 Vishera River in encyclopedia of Perm Krai]\n* [http://slovari.yandex.ru/~\u043a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0438/\u0411\u0421\u042d/\u0412\u0438\u0448\u0435\u0440\u0430%20(\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0430%20\u0432%20\u041f\u0435\u0440\u043c\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439%20\u043e\u0431\u043b.)/ Vishera in Great Soviet Encyclopedia]\n{{Kama River}}\n[[Category:Rivers of Perm Krai]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses|Vishera River (disambiguation)}}\n{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}}\n\n{{Infobox river\n| name              = Vishera River\n| image             = Vishera.jpg\n| image_size        = \n| image_alt         =\n| image_caption     = View of the [[Tulymsky Kamen]] mountain range from the banks of the Vishera\n| map               = Kama basin.png\n| map_size          = 200 \n| map_alt           =\n| map_caption       = Scheme of the Kama River Basin.\n| source1_location  = North Ural\n| mouth             = [[Kama River]]\n| subdivision_type1 = Country\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Russia]]\n| progression       = {{RKama}}\n| length            = {{convert|415|km|mi|abbr=on}} \n| source1_elevation = \n| mouth_coordinates = {{coord|59|54|14|N|56|26|20|E|source:kolossus-ruwiki|display=it}}\n| discharge1_avg    = {{convert|457|m3/s|cuft/s|abbr=on}} \n| basin_size        = {{convert|31,200|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} \n| tributaries_left  =\n| tributaries_right =\n}}\n\nThe '''Vishera River''' ({{lang-ru|\u0412\u0438\u0448\u0435\u0440\u0430}}) is a river in [[Perm Krai]], [[Russia]], a [[:wikt:left bank|left bank]] tributary of the [[Kama River]]. It is {{convert|415|km|mi}} long, and its [[drainage basin]] covers {{convert|31200|km2|mi2}}.<ref name=gvr>[http://textual.ru/gvr/index.php?card=180376 \u00ab\u0420\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0412\u0418\u0428\u0415\u0420\u0410\u00bb], Russian State Water Registry</ref><ref>http://www.feow.org/ecoregion_details.php?eco=410</ref> The Vishera River freezes in late October or early November and stays under the ice until the end of April. There are [[diamond]] deposits in the basin of the Vishera River.\n\nThe Vishera used to be part of the [[Cherdyn Road]] and is still considered one of the most picturesque rivers of the Urals. It starts on the extreme northeast of Perm Krai, near the border with the [[Komi Republic]] and [[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]. It flows on the west foothills of Ural Mountains and is a mountain river for most of its length. There are many rapids and shoals in the channel and many rocks along its banks. \n\nThe [[Vishera Nature Reserve]] is along the upper reaches of the river.\n\n'''Main tributaries (from source to mouth):'''<ref name=gvr/>\n* Left: [[Niols River|Niols]], [[Moyva River|Moyva]], [[Vels River|Vels]], [[Uls River|Uls]], [[Akchim River|Akchim]], [[Yazva River|Yazva]], [[Vizhaikha River|Vizhaikha]];\n* Right: [[Lypiya River|Lypiya]], [[Yelva River|Yelva]], [[Bolshaya Vaya River|Bolshaya Vaya]], [[Pisanka River|Pisanka]], [[Govorukha River|Govorukha]], [[Kolva River, Perm Krai|Kolva]].\n\n== Etymology ==\nKomi people call the river ''Viser''. Experts in the Komi language noticed that this element is also in names of other rivers in Ural. [[Aleksandr Matveyev (linguist)|A. K. Matveyev]] supposes that Vishera can mean ''Northern River'' or ''Midnight River'' (in [[Sami languages]]).\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://enc.permculture.ru/showObject.do?object=1803757360&idParentObject=1803883941 Vishera River in encyclopedia of Perm Krai]\n* [http://slovari.yandex.ru/~\u043a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0438/\u0411\u0421\u042d/\u0412\u0438\u0448\u0435\u0440\u0430%20(\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0430%20\u0432%20\u041f\u0435\u0440\u043c\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439%20\u043e\u0431\u043b.)/ Vishera in Great Soviet Encyclopedia]\n{{Kama River}}\n[[Category:Rivers of Perm Krai]]\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vishera_River_(Perm_Krai)"}
